node.text: Nah if they allow things to go back to normal, welcome to the 2nd wave baby
@joseph_yu03

[JUST IN] This is because CB measures "have shown promise in reducing Covid-19 infections locally in the community", Gan said.

If the number of new cases of infection continues to be low, Singapore can allow more economic and social activities to be restored.

#linkinbio

Photo by Mothership staff
don care abt foreign workers ah?
Reboot SG life please 🙏😩
@winnie.ash98 🥳🥳🥳❤️❤️❤️
@maddly_in_love
Hopefully it ends on 1st June 2020. But If the condition gets worse, higher chance it might be extended again. So lets hope for the Circuit Breaker to end on 1st June 2020. #letsfightcovid19together
Honestly I’d love the idea for it to stop but just keep it a lil longer. Cuz I sure ass hell ain’t gonna wait for a 2nd wave
I wanna gym!!!

We’re all in this shit because China spread their Wuhan virus, we pay the price for something that’s not our doing 
Screw you CCP 🖕🏻 Hopefully this cb ends soon and we will have freedom

👍👏😍 this is good news for seniors to come down  walk around the void deck to have light exercise and looking at green turf good for their eyes .Reserve seats for disable seniors to rest for a while not taking meals. I am.sure our neighbouring hood will be please.👴👵
Best news I've heard all month! Let's keep it up Singaporeans!
The country looks better now that no one stays outside
@piguyangyang
so i guess our foreign workers arent part of the community huh
@afr0dyte

Singapore should not ease the measures. Other countries made this mistake and are potentially paying the price for it again. There is no vaccine yet and the measures are the ones keeping the virus under control. Example, HK, after 23 days of 0 cases suddenly popped up 2 local cases somehow.

whatever cases it is, it all happens in Singapore so actually they shouldn’t be letting 1June to be the last day. 
You shouldn’t separate local and foreigners amount to think that it is in low number. It all happens in singapore then singapore should handle it not just only caring for local or your stupid economics or eduction to bring face to this country. 
May19 some students will be going back to school, and until now the numbers are still between 600-800. Just because local cases are small, doesn’t mean you can allow this to be on going. 
Virus is not joke, it takes at least 1-2 years to actually slowly get back to normal. There’s no point rushing economic in such situation. 
1 week 6 days after some students get back to school is 1June. Adults going back to work. Others getting out of their home altogether. There it goes, out of control. hell man.
Nah if they allow things to go back to normal, welcome to the 2nd wave baby
@joseph_yu03
